                    <h1>QuickBooks Vendors API</h1>
                    <p>
                        After your Major application connects with QuickBooks, all vendors stored in QuickBooks are imported into the Major database. You can query these vendors based on their name. Additionally, you can query all vendors at once.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Retrieving an Existing Vendor or Vendors</h2>
                    <p>
                        <code><strong>GET</strong><br>https://majorapi.com/api/quickbooks/vendors</code>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <code><strong>GET</strong><br>https://majorapi.com/api/quickbooks/vendors/{vendorName}</code>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Note</strong> &mdash; Vendors are retrieved by their name. If the name has a space in it, it must be URL encoded properly. The name does not have to be capitalized; Major will handle normalizing the name
                        to best attempt to locate the vendor.
                    </p>

                    <h3>Successful Request and Response</h3>

                    <h4>200 Ok</h4>
<pre>curl -X GET \
